OL,3,CPaddleboard company boss 'not remotely
OL,4,Cqualified' to lead trip which killed
OL,5,Cfour
OL,7,FThe owner of a paddleboarding company
OL,8,Fwas "not remotely qualified" to lead a
OL,9,Ftour in which four people died, a
OL,10,Fcourt has heard.
OL,12,FMorgan Rogers, 24, Nicola Wheatley,
OL,13,F40, Paul O'Dwyer, 42, and Andrea
OL,14,FPowell, 41, died as a result of the
OL,15,Fincident on 30 October 2021 on the
OL,16,FRiver Cleddau in Haverfordwest,
OL,17,FPembrokeshire, when their paddleboards
OL,18,Fwent over a weir during "extremely
OL,19,Fhazardous conditions".
